section.p:
		Many students will say that they sometimes "forget" how to do arithmetic with fractions. This often results from
		viewing fractions as purely a collection of symbols with particular rules for how to manipulate them. Their
		forgetfulness sometimes leads them to guess at how to work with fractions. Here are some examples:
		
			\begin{array}{ccc}
    			\dfrac{3}{5} + \dfrac{8}{5} \overset{\times}{=} \dfrac{3 + 8}{5 + 5} = \dfrac{11}{10}
					\amp \qquad \qquad \amp
					\dfrac{2}{5} + \dfrac{5}{6} \overset{\times}{=} \dfrac{2 + 5}{5 \cdot 6} = \dfrac{7}{30} \\ \\
			    \dfrac{4}{5} - \dfrac{1}{3} \overset{\times}{=} \dfrac{4 - 1}{5 - 3} = \dfrac{3}{2}
					\amp \qquad \qquad \amp
					\hspace{2cm} \dfrac{3}{5} - \dfrac{1}{3} \overset{\times}{=} \dfrac{3 - 1}{5 \cdot 3} = \dfrac{2}{15}
			\end{array}

